main event: Two balloon-like objects were observed in the sky traveling in a westerly direction over Honolulu, Hawai'i on July 20, 1949.
interesting points: The first object was a balloon-like object, followed by a second balloon-like object which appeared to circle the first., The sighting occurred on a clear morning between 10:30 and 11:00 a.m., A local resident, Mrs. Arnold, was behind her house when she made the observation., Fleet Weather Central confirmed a radiosonde was launched at the same time, which could account for one of the sightings., Official sources could not explain the origin of the balloon-like objects observed.
witness description: Mrs. Arnold, who reported the sighting while doing laundry behind her house.
